[[Translation:en/Archive/OpenTTD/Comparison of OpenTTD and TTDPatch features]]
If you have played [[en/Archive/OpenTTD/TTDPatch]] a lot, you will notice that many similar things are implemented differently in OpenTTD. Not all features are [[en/Manual/Interoperability|compatible]] with TTDPatch.
*[[en/Manual/Interoperability|Quick savegame conversion guide]]

==Features that are significantly different in OpenTTD==
Notice: List is currently incomplete
*Real [[en/Manual/Waypoints]].
*New AI.
*Two new [[en/Manual/Bridges]] instead of raise Bridges speed limit.
*[[en/Drag and drop]] for most tools.
*[[en/Manual/Convert rail]] (from and to rail, monorail, maglev).
*[[en/Manual/Sell entire train]].
*New buttons in GUI instead of shortcuts.
*Drag and Drop signals (Auto-[[en/Manual/Signals]]).
*Configure [[en/Community/Patches/Patches]] inside the game instead of using a third-party program.
*[[en/Manual/Landscaping]] toolbar.
*Servicing intervals in percentage of max. reliability.
*Ability to sort vehicles list by different properties.
*More detailed performance ratings.
*[[en/Manual/Extra Viewport]].
*Ability to [[en/Manual/Move company HQ]].
*[[en/Archive/Manual/Magic bulldozer]] cheat to remove industries etc.
*Ability to make [[en/Archive/Manual/Settings/Nonuniform stations]]

==TTDPatch features in OpenTTD==
These features work exactly the same as in [[en/Archive/OpenTTD/TTDPatch]]. Some of them need to be activated in the [[en/Archive/Manual/Settings/Configuring patches]].<br/>
